<h1><a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/cctools/">Creative Commons Tools</a></h1>

<p>The <a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/cctools/">cctools sourceforge project</a> is a collection of tools for using <a href="http://creativecommons.org/metadata/">license metadata</a> from <a href="http://creativecommons.org/">Creative Commons</a>.</p>

<p>Questions, comments, and criticism (all most welcome) should be directed to the <a href="http://creativecommons.org/discuss#metadata">cc-metadata mailing list</a>.</p>

<h2>Tools</h2>

<h3>ccTag tools</h3>

<p>A set of tools for tagging and validating CC licenses in audio files. 
Currently only supports MP3, with OGG support coming soon.</p>

<p>Most dependencies are maintained in vendor branches in 
<a href="http://cvs.sourceforge.net/viewcvs.py/cctools/cctag-gui">CVS</a>.

<ul>
 <li><a href="http://cvs.sourceforge.net/viewcvs.py/cctools/cctag-gui/cctag.py?rev=HEAD">ccTag</a>: a cross-platform, graphical interface for embedding licenses.  Requires <a href="http://wxpython.org">wxPython</a>.</li>
 <li><a href="http://cvs.sourceforge.net/viewcvs.py/cctools/cctag-gui/cct.py?rev=HEAD">cct.py</a>: a command-line interface for embedding licenses.</li>
 <li><a href="http://cvs.sourceforge.net/viewcvs.py/cctools/cctag-gui/ccl.py?rev=HEAD">ccl.py</a>: a command-line interface for looking up and verifying embedded licenses.</li>
</ul>

<h3>ccwebsearch</h3>

<p>A prototype web search engine for Creative Commons licensed works.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://search.creativecommons.org/">Live installation</li>
<li><a href="http://sourceforge.net/cvs/?group_id=80503">CVS</a> (ccwebsearch module)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Related Projects</h2>

<p><strong><a href="http://aetherial.net/Verify/">Verify</a></strong> is an OS X app that verifies embedded license information in MP3 files per the guidelines mentioned above.</p>

<p><strong><a href="http://cclicense.sourceforge.net/">CCLicense</a></strong> is a simple library written in pure PHP that helps developers utilize and integrate the Creative Commons  licenses in their own programs.</p>

<p><strong><a href="http://workspaces.gotdotnet.com/cclib">CCLicenseLib</a></strong> is a library for C#.</p>

<p><strong><a href="http://yergler.net/projects/ccrdf">ccRdf</a></strong> is a library for Python.</p>

<p><strong><a href="http://www.yergler.net/projects/ccvalidator/">ccvalidator</a></strong> is a Python toolkit and application to read and validate CC license data.</p>

<p><strong><a href="http://www.yergler.net/projects/mozcc/">mozCC</a></strong> is an extension for Mozilla Firebird to highlight license information embedded in web pages.</p>

